                    <note xml:lang="en" type="abstract">In hagiography:
                            <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1483">Shirin</persName> and her
                        two children were martyrs from <placeName>Beth Zadoq</placeName>. She was
                        baking bread when she learned of 12000 martyrs under <persName>Yazdegerd
                            II</persName>. She took herself and her children before the governor and
                        confessed her Christian faith to him. She and her children were
                        decapitated.</note>
